e^{-x}
e^{-x}=1-x+{x^2\over2!}-{x^3\over3!}+\cdots
\cos x = \frac{e^{ix}+e^{-ix}}{2}
e^{-x}\cos x = \frac{e^{x(-1+i)} + e^{x(-1-i)}}2
e^{-x}\cos x = \sum_{n=0}^\infty \frac{a_nx^n}{n!}
a_n = \frac{(-1+i)^n + (-1-i)^n} 2  = \Re{(-1+i)^n}
-1+i = \sqrt{2}e^{i\frac{3\pi}{4}}
(-1+i)^n
(\sqrt{2})^n \cos\left(\frac{3\pi n}4\right)
e^{-x}\cos x = \sum_{n=0}^\infty 2^{\frac n 2}\cos\left(\frac{3\pi n}4\right)\frac{x^n}{n!}
a_n=2^{\frac{n}2}\cos(\frac{3\pi n}4)
